B.WL=new A.lq("Exterior screens or a paracord curtain",B.cQ,null,"Hang on the outside","Insect screening, or lengths of cord hung about 4 inches apart down the outside face. Both break up the reflection, and they also soften the blow of any bird that still comes in.","You see straight through screening from inside, like a screen door. Hanging cord reads as fine vertical lines from the street, but vanishes at a distance.",B.oc)
B.WG=new A.lq("Exterior dot film, BirdTape, or a dense decal grid",B.cQ,"Comes in dark or white. Dark shows against bright, sky-reflecting glass; white shows against dark glass \u2014 shade, trees, or a wall behind it. Pick whichever contrasts with what your window reflects.","Apply to outside of glass","Markers across the whole pane, spaced no more than 2 inches apart. The small spacing is important, since birds fly at any gap that looks big enough for them to fit through.","Small dots read as a faint texture from inside and disappear from a few steps back. They come in patterns you choose, so this can look deliberate rather than medical.",B.oc)
B.WI=new A.lq("A tempera paint or soap design",B.cQ,"Tempera comes in any colour; soap dries pale. Use a dark colour on bright, sky-reflecting glass and a pale one \u2014 or the soap \u2014 on dark glass, so the pattern stands out against the reflection.","Apply to outside of glass","Must be placed 2 inches apart or less. Draw on by hand with tempera (poster) paint or a bar of dry soap. This fix is cheap and removable. Tempera holds up for months outdoors; soap is fainter and needs redoing after heavy rain.","This fix looks hand-made and can be made into a personalized pattern. This fix is most common as a grid, but can be done with illustrations, so long as the lines remain no more than 2 inches apart.",B.oc)
B.oe=new A.e5([B.cQ,B.m1],t.Z4)
B.WH=new A.lq("Perforated one-way film over the full pane",B.cQ,null,"Apply to outside of glass","A printed film shot through with tiny holes. It looks near-solid from outside, so there is no mirror, and close to clear from inside.","From the street it looks like lightly tinted glass, and it can be printed with any pattern or image you like. Your view out is slightly dimmed but does not obscure everything.",B.oe)
B.WF=new A.lq("Exterior shades, awnings, or shutters",B.cQ,null,"Hang on the outside","Anything that physically shades the glass while the sun is on it will remove the mirror effect. It may be a more expensive one-time buy, but it also cuts your cooling costs.","This is the only fix that puts nothing on the glass and looks like architecture rather than as a bird product.",B.oe)
B.a0r=new A.e5([B.rb],t.Z4)
B.WM=new A.lq("Close blinds or curtains after dark",null,null,"Hang on the inside","After dark, when many migrating birds fly, closing your blinds keeps interior light from spilling out and pulling down migrating birds.","Quick and undoable in a second, and changes nothing about how the house looks from outside.",B.a0r)
B.WK=new A.lq("Fritted, etched, or angled glass",B.cQ,null,"Part of the glass","Bird-safe glazing, for a replacement or a new build. Fritted glass has a ceramic pattern fired into its outer surface; etched glass has it cut in. Angled glazing is tilted a few degrees toward the ground, it mirrors the earth rather than the sky, so there is no open air to fly at. This is costly, but is one time and does not need to be maintained or reapplied.","Patterns run from nearly invisible to a deliberate design feature, and the choice is yours at order time.",B.oe)
B.a0o=new A.e5([B.ra],t.Z4)
B.WJ=new A.lq("Move the feeder closer than 3 ft or further than 10 ft",null,null,null,"You can move your feeder within 3 feet from your window so that a bird cannot build up enough speed to be hurt, or move it past 10 feet so that it has room to see the glass and veer off.",null,B.a0o)
B.Uh=s([B.WL,B.WG,B.WI,B.WH,B.WF,B.WM,B.WK,B.WJ],A.ab("o<lq>"))
